        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733886_839739_14825" xmi:uuid="e83b431a-54a7-49f7-8a88-04df15685811" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733484_497882_14061"/>
          <body>A PropertyDefinition is the definition of a property.&#13; It is used in ObjectWithPropertyDefinitions that is then inherited by many of the objects in the MethodologyManagement capability.&#13; &lt;example&gt;A PropertyDefinition may reflect physics or arbitrary user defined measurements.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ManagedObject therefore, it may have a ClassifiedAs string to define the type of property.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;Organizations may be classified as "airline" and these may then have a property classified as for example "route", or "range".&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;Properties do not have individual traceability outside of the object to which they are part. If traceability is needed, or exposure of the properties to other objects, then DistributionValueType for Uncertainty, KeyValueType or Verification Status should be used.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>PropertyDefinition</name>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1585576226532_236947_75754" xmi:uuid="95258607-50be-48cb-a235-a64aa5473c55" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590573652664_871724_67233" xmi:uuid="5795b11c-5129-4d08-944f-e264a9470ce8" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1585576226532_236947_75754"/>
            <body>The Unit shall be specified for all instances of numerical PropertyDefinition.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>UnitsContraint</name>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1585576226532_259492_75755" xmi:uuid="0474b619-d800-44d0-bb3b-a457562648cf" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>The Unit shall be specified for all instances of numerical PropertyDefinition.</body>
            <language>English</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590581105290_319783_90913" xmi:uuid="aacc2ce7-efe1-4978-9c0c-0bfbe75d45ed" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590581105294_752422_90915" xmi:uuid="3f194934-d327-4f9c-9434-6448b2e7c44c" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1590581105290_319783_90913"/>
            <body>values shall be subClassof the reference data class.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>ValueTypeConstraint</name>
          <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1585562588137_830173_71503"/>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590581105294_320857_90914" xmi:uuid="bc0390ac-bf60-4dd1-8624-e0ef05f23ad8" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>ValueType.mustBeSubClassOf('http://standards.iso.org/iso/10303/-243/tech/refdata/ap243_v1#83615252-c407-47c3-bec5-9b3c1945703e')</body>
            <language>OCL2.0</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733886_111095_14824" xmi:uuid="845d3586-b225-47eb-bbc7-e738eb7d0466" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
          <general xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733484_59641_14064"/>
        </generalization>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733886_738293_14826" xmi:uuid="06be9d9a-358c-4956-811e-6479b395264d" xmi:type="uml:Property">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734596_775332_16951" xmi:uuid="8703bf0d-9b48-4772-a496-cd1133a89187" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733886_738293_14826"/>
            <body>the ExternalUnit with which the quantity is expressed for numerical valueTypes. The value of this attribute need not be specified (see note). &lt;note&gt;It is optional because some properties are without units.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;The unit shall be specified for all numerical property definitions.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;Examples of properties without units are colour.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;example&gt;Numerical values without dimensions but with units are percentage and ratio.&lt;/example&gt;</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>Unit</name>
          <visibility>public</visibility>
          <type href="../../../Core_model/CommonResources/CommonResources.xmi#_ExternalUnit"/>
