    <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_180432_14048" xmi:uuid="2b4b748a-2cff-4263-9ef0-8cc4a8aae64f" xmi:type="uml:Package">
      <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512581460340_28232_33895" xmi:uuid="404ea918-9b51-4476-b02d-1f6ba595c9d7" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
        <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_180432_14048"/>
        <body>This capability enables the representation of a system parent-child structure, known as a Breakdown in a collaborative context. A Breakdown consists of BreakdownElements representing the subsystems of the system. Different types of breakdowns and breakdown elements are distinguished, such as functional and physical. It also allows cross associations between elements for the definition of assignments. Items that realise BreakdownElements can be identified. &lt;note&gt;The boundaries and interconnections between the subsystems are defined using the Interfaces capability.&lt;/note&gt; The Ffigure below provides an overview of this capability. &lt;figuresysml&gt;&lt;id&gt;_18_4_1_1b310459_1578988065329_558577_58877&lt;/id&gt;Overview of the Breakdown capability&lt;/figuresysml&gt;</body>
      </ownedComment>
      <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1585644826453_615564_73561" xmi:uuid="bc507612-09fb-4d56-9696-1d7c56c940b7" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
        <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734006_252689_15555"/>
        <body>to do: convert Breakdown Enums to xxxReferenceData blocks.</body>
      </ownedComment>
