      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_171579_14435" xmi:uuid="51862def-4b85-42c8-829c-78e348553df6" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734006_856990_15519" xmi:uuid="2aaea01e-ef08-4d67-a327-44b2068042dd" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_171579_14435"/>
          <body>A BreakdownElementStructuralAssociation is the relationship that structures the Breakdown. It is the equivalent of a "parent-child" relationship or "system to subsystem" relationship, though it is not a strict tree structure because the relationships may cross reference if necessary, therefore, a child may have many parents. &lt;example&gt;Aircraft BreakdownElement is a parent of Fuselage BreakdownElement that is a parent of CentreBox BreakdownElement, but Aircraft BreakdownElement is also the parent of WingTipToTip BreakdownElement is also a parent of CentreBox BreakdownElement, therefore, the CentreBox may have two parents.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is intended (though not constrained) that the BreakdownElements are in the same Breakdown.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It may be the Context for an Assumption.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1568708384357_544689_48807" xmi:uuid="5da09743-3f00-4cab-a64f-ad74b9f789f0" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1509609654909_367214_32565"/>
          <body>core_v1: relationship object: breakdown element view relationship : hierarchy breakdown element view relationship</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>BreakdownElementStructuralAssociation</name>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139346462_268718_32565" xmi:uuid="c5668804-5077-41a8-be5d-cdb941fd7e07" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512734030815_273009_34531" xmi:uuid="7fea1848-5324-462e-bda2-72e0bb79b1bb" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139346462_268718_32565"/>
            <body>The Parent shall not be the same as the Child</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>parentNotChild</name>
          <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_171579_14435"/>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139346462_741199_32566" xmi:uuid="d1ea7253-f450-4426-97f2-3c5db7596298" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>self.Parent &lt;&gt; self.Child</body>
            <language>OCL2.0</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1586175545160_915973_74964" xmi:uuid="08740af6-9bfb-4694-b8bb-707020398893" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
