      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_683739_14437" xmi:uuid="c6973ee4-5013-4ebd-b637-762f8a8d7313" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734006_317931_15536" xmi:uuid="88c59c6d-f302-4a15-bc91-497d7d30ab0d" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_683739_14437"/>
          <body>A BreakdownElementAssociation is the relationship between BreakdownElements that is not structural. &lt;note&gt;It is assumed that the BreakdownElements are in different Breakdowns though this is not mandatory.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ManagedObject therefore, an association between two elements can be ClassifiedAs.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;ClassifiedAs "impact of change" and a DistributionValueInstance assigned using the ValueOf property.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;example&gt;Classified as "Allocation" for allocating a functional BreakdownElement "provide lift" to a physical BreakdownElement "Wing".&lt;/example&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1568730227459_143935_51345" xmi:uuid="a78311b3-59d4-4c6b-9eef-a5c1eb44361e" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1509527360459_835215_37316"/>
          <body>subclassOf=core_v1:relationship object: breakdown element version relationship prefLabel= breakdown element association</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>BreakdownElementAssociation</name>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139402667_82393_32567" xmi:uuid="6d8aa525-3234-4940-ac54-5eba2d8496a4" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
