      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733876_514537_14811" xmi:uuid="d534b755-367b-4dc5-b37b-416405333201" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734596_374800_16900" xmi:uuid="cbacebe6-a849-4f2e-8733-fa29b235992d" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733876_514537_14811"/>
          <body>&lt;note&gt;These designated data types may realize a Component or ComponentAssemblyUsage. This excludes: &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Breakdowns, BreakdownElementAssociations;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;ActualActivity;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Documents, DigitalFile;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;RequirementShouldBeSatisfied, Verification;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Person, Organization;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;PropertyDefinition, PropertyValue;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Approval;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;All SecurityTrust (Contract, SecurityClassification &amp; InformationRight);&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;all relationship objects that are just types of ManagedObject.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>ComponentRealizationItem</name>
        <isAbstract>true</isAbstract>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1562660183050_827057_50524" xmi:uuid="f061cad1-de92-472d-95eb-7c05520308aa" xmi:type="uml:Port">
          <name>componentRealizationItem</name>
          <visibility>public</visibility>
          <type href="../../../Core_model/Collection/Collection.xmi#_18_4_1_1b310459_1581932043631_158459_57465"/>
          <aggregation>composite</aggregation>
        </ownedAttribute>
      </packagedElement>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_238939_14439" xmi:uuid="dcee1e58-97c6-4df4-ada4-a0a9e36e13a5" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1585671075186_211677_95013" xmi:uuid="0148e7af-0c7b-4ab2-b3b6-075bcc508ead" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1585670924778_826251_94956"/>
          <body>breakdown of</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734006_46844_15552" xmi:uuid="4d9c2509-a21e-4347-89f1-8248fcf56793" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_238939_14439"/>
          <body>A Breakdown is a partitioning of a system into a structured set of subsystems known as BreakdownElement objects. It is a BreakdownOf something and has a Type property representing the purpose of the Breakdown, this shall not &#13;reference a BreakdownElement that is also an Element in the Breakdown &lt;note&gt;The Type property can be used to apply business rules to control the types of Elements [BreakdownElements] that can be added to the Breakdowns. Alternatively the Breakdown may use the ClassifiedAs property inherited from ManagedObject to allow tailoring by business rules.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of VersionableObject therefore, it shall have at least one VersionIdentifiers property.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Parent-child relationships are represented by BreakdownElementStructuralAssociation.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Allocations or associations between BreakdownsElements are represented by BreakdownElementAssociation.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of VersionableObject therefore, it has a VersionIdentifiers property. It is also a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it has Identifiers and may have a descriptions and names and other management information.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1568715374995_389886_49099" xmi:uuid="b73f2aab-ed8d-4c55-8255-d12f10d5171f" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734006_252689_15555"/>
          <body>subClassOf=core_v1:breakdown:functional breakdown subClassOf=core_v1:breakdown:physical breakdown core_v1:breakdown:system breakdown: prefLabel=logical breakdown core_v1:breakdown:zonal breakdown: prefLabel= spatial breakdown</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>Breakdown</name>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590590565774_564237_99039" xmi:uuid="586ad775-7feb-45c6-93cc-8bea36a0fa6d" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590590565778_310755_99041" xmi:uuid="92a4cf06-6760-4ed6-b285-266c2412bbea" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1590590565774_564237_99039"/>
            <body>values shall be subClassof the reference data class.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>TypeConstraint</name>
          <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734006_252689_15555"/>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590590565778_933340_99040" xmi:uuid="195100c5-df13-42ad-a25b-ff01376563cd" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>Type.mustBeSubClassOf('http://standards.iso.org/iso/10303/-4000/tech/refdata/core_v1#89084bb0-130a-0135-b552-598f1b1392ae')</body>
            <language>OCL2.0</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139713477_753331_32842" xmi:uuid="f1e2f6a5-4ca1-4035-ba18-333f51a4908d" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139898130_441302_32858" xmi:uuid="91ad485f-dbdf-4a1d-8e09-29f05a88c900" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139713477_753331_32842"/>
            <body>the Breakdown shall not have what it is a BreakdownOf as an element to prevent a circular definition.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>notRecursive</name>
          <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_238939_14439"/>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510139713477_866696_32843" xmi:uuid="bf7b26c7-48a5-407b-ad92-45903c70ada0" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>self.Element-&gt;forAll(e | self.BreakdownOf &lt;&gt; e) </body>
            <language>OCL2.0</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1586176032428_727530_75280" xmi:uuid="32563f15-ddd2-4a9b-ac12-45fafdfd12e8" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
