      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_585955_14438" xmi:uuid="f58e94cb-6849-44ce-95a4-7bce03f4ba29" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1585841396645_286879_85437" xmi:uuid="89bf304b-7d6e-451e-8339-c856d727f1e1" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <body>Enhancement: Consider updating to have a to "context" associations "from" these association-objects to the Architecture rather than the inclusion to the objects. &gt; "Context" is more in-keeping with rest of BOM &gt; The current layout is more PLCS-like - i.e. more generic, but will we need to distinguish at some point between object inclusions and association inclusions? Consider: 1. are associations to only one context (like CMT ModelTypeIsDerivedFrom)...I think no 2. may context be 0, or is there always a context if therefore what is the "always" MethodologyLibrary equivalent? 3. What apart from architecture may be the context - i.e. shall point to an interface? 4. Is contextItem interface, is it the same for all association-objects?... for all breakdownAssociation objects?</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734006_349238_15545" xmi:uuid="aca3b181-484e-4cc0-9bf0-edaffcf73573" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733746_585955_14438"/>
          <body>ComponentRealizationAssociation is an association between a Component, or ComponentAssemblyUsage and something else that is a realization of that component. &lt;note&gt;Identification that the association is in the context of an Architecture is represented by ArchitectureElementInclusion.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;The other thing may be a model that represents the object.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It may be the Subject or Context for an Assumption or Justification.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It may have Approvals.&lt;/note&gt;</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576503488434_920841_71057" xmi:uuid="eca49a91-15cc-429d-88d1-b4804e024ab3" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1521617863033_512803_39095"/>
          <body>realization association collection UUID from ComponentRealizationAssociation subclass of core_v1#collection</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>ComponentRealizationAssociation</name>
