    </packagedElement>
    <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_497906_14044" xmi:uuid="3365a054-0929-4cf6-9217-7ddf61e49408" xmi:type="uml:Package">
      <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512658295376_771058_32671" xmi:uuid="ed7ffbe0-2812-4b66-bba0-67956f045873" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
        <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_497906_14044"/>
        <body>This capability enables the representation of model and key value definitions, and also the representation of templates for specifying how definitions may be derived from other definitions in a collaborative context. It includes the representation of methods to be used, with an identification of resources and input and output types with restrictions required by the method. The Figure below provides an overview of this capability. &lt;figuresysml&gt;&lt;id&gt;_18_4_1_1b310459_1578991032291_606302_66758&lt;/id&gt;Overview of the Methodology Management capability&lt;/figuresysml&gt;</body>
      </ownedComment>
      <name>MethodologyManagement</name>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734406_899082_16447" xmi:uuid="007542fd-a9c9-4af0-bb2f-a55965d91df4" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734886_471805_18299" xmi:uuid="7690d7fc-4633-4c3f-ad31-33c8c59c38c1" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734406_899082_16447"/>
          <body>A MethodInputAssignment is the assignment of and input type to a Method or ApplicableMethod. &lt;note&gt;The InputFor shall be a reference to an instance of a Method when the referenced InputType is an input in all usages of the Method. When the referenced InputType is an input in specific usages of the Method the InputFor shall reference an instance of an ApplicableMethod that shall then reference the method.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject. The Name or Identifiers can be used by the Method to distinguish between inputs of the same type.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;A method to construct a torus surface using a loft construction approach has two inputs of type "circular curve"; a "profile" and a "guide". Two MethodInputAssignment instances are used, both referencing the same "Circular Curve" ModelType, but having different Names of "profile" and "guide".&lt;/example&gt; &#13;&lt;note&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyValues therefore, it may have PropertyValues specific to the use of the input for the method.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;For properties on an input that are related to an output, then Sensitivity is used.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;Properties may be the limitations of the acceptable input range.&lt;/example&gt;</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576743560280_931823_56029" xmi:uuid="a25089c3-8fe5-4674-b5b1-31e0219bdd92" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1548950612733_205253_81632"/>
          <body>activity method input assignment sub class of core_v1#activity method assignment</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>MethodInputAssignment</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1586171765613_370772_73405" xmi:uuid="1044fe55-ee53-45f2-b9e0-c6cf9aa645ed" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
          <general xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733786_981753_14561"/>
        </generalization>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734886_63426_18295" xmi:uuid="984f75b5-b90b-41aa-86d5-175accdb7608" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
