      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733656_615235_14225" xmi:uuid="6781f712-7af4-414e-b0bd-eea84ccf9888" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576504681051_89371_71179" xmi:uuid="1f9596d2-0aa2-4ec9-95e9-a0ee4e3b161e" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576504800129_703586_71193"/>
          <body>assembly constituent relationship sub class of: core_rd_v1# next assembly view usage</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576745700641_136453_59051" xmi:uuid="8db66011-9ece-4415-b1ab-2fd102c0f635" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508150666497_747970_37798"/>
          <body>model part sub type of core_rd_v1#general part</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733926_252573_15136" xmi:uuid="a9181cc8-bec6-4c9d-8e1f-7c8cbe39ba2b" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733656_615235_14225"/>
          <body>A ModelType is the definition of a model managed at the collaborative level. &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyDefinitions therefore, it may define the PropertyDefinitions of the properties that are to be extracted from the instance (ModelInstance). The PropertyDefinitions are used for properties specific to this ModelType. If the property is a key piece of information that can be extracted from several ModelType, then KeyValueType should be used instead.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;Some examples of models are: design; analysis; systems definition; reports; specifications.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;The definition can include the levels of granularity of data.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;Some examples of granularity level are: single parameter value; a 1-D line/curve/vector; 2-D/3-D matrix/surface/diagram/solid; composite set of multi-dimensional data.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of VersionableObject therefore, it shall have at least one VersionIdentifiers property.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyDefinitions therefore, it may define the PropertyDefinitions for properties that can be added to the ModelInstance that IsAnInstanceOf this ModelType.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of MethodologyObject therefore, it may include FormalDocumentation and InformalDocumentation to define the ModelType.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification that it can be a resource for a Method is represented by MethodResourceAssignment.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification that it can be an input for a Method is represented by MethodInputAssignment.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification of the items it is DerivedFrom is represented by ModelTypeIsDerivedFrom.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification of KeyValueTypes that can be extracted from it is represented by KeyValueTypeIsExtractedFrom.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576662574136_360314_56755" xmi:uuid="bf4865b0-a569-4c67-8fbc-744f62f2ccb5" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508152329944_964430_39998"/>
          <body>inherits from part version relationship sub class of: core_rd_v1#hierarchy part version relationship</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>ModelType</name>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510143278323_406721_34617" xmi:uuid="b2584b69-a610-48ff-8e55-d2f648080a7b" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1513009037091_526934_35425" xmi:uuid="a9d8a4ca-0eb9-4f68-a7b4-0f4757e27e0c" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1510143278323_406721_34617"/>
            <body>A ModelType shall not inherit from itself.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>notInheritsFromSelf</name>
          <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733656_615235_14225"/>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1510143278323_784945_34618" xmi:uuid="24ad0bce-dea6-4c0f-bf36-b5f95a7e30c1" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>self.InheritsFrom-&gt;excludes(self)</body>
            <language>OCL2.0</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1586182420146_533105_83627" xmi:uuid="0393e026-2808-4ea5-9a57-406a0d6bc543" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
