        <ownedAttribute xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733926_599811_15138" xmi:uuid="00bcb7b6-9f9a-43aa-a317-bb3fe4329ded" xmi:type="uml:Property">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512736940498_865679_35957" xmi:uuid="899cac4d-f91e-4a41-9ea1-059062ee580d" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733926_599811_15138"/>
            <body>the instances of ModelType from which characteristics are inherited. The value of this attribute need not be specified. &lt;note&gt;This is the concatenation of the ModelType characteristics, rather than inheritance in the computing language sense.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;"wing mesh model type" and "engine mesh model type" may inherit from "mesh model type", therefore, they shall obey the definition of "mesh model type" as well as their own specific definitions.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It can also be used to specify generic Methods that may be applicable to all models of the same ModelType.&lt;/note&gt;</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>InheritsFrom</name>
          <visibility>public</visibility>
