      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733656_785126_14222" xmi:uuid="fbc371b3-bd67-4da6-93e6-868739857969" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733926_430902_15109" xmi:uuid="13f46890-5b62-4e99-b641-f3a661bb6c24" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733656_785126_14222"/>
          <body>The MethodResourceAssignment is the assignment of a referenced item as a resource for a Method. &lt;example&gt;A method may use a surrogate model. The surrogate model is a ModelInstance which will have traceability to the results data used to create the surrogate.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject. The Name or Identifiers can be used by the Method to distinguish between resources.&lt;/note&gt;&#13; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyValues therefore, it may have PropertyValues specific to the use of the resource for the method.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;A property may be used to specify the quality of resource such as the number of licenses needed by the method.&lt;/example&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>MethodResourceAssignment</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1548952541425_313402_84119" xmi:uuid="02d3d960-54b4-4e70-a11f-1977f158d254" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
