    <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_751541_14043" xmi:uuid="7842614a-e6bd-4450-b7fe-6f503b4dbd33" xmi:type="uml:Package">
      <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512638341842_51645_32529" xmi:uuid="9e08e9c9-16d4-4e5b-8ea6-77d64e2ddde1" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
        <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_751541_14043"/>
        <body>The requirements and verification capability enables definition of requirements, how they should be satisfied and verified in a collaborative context. Requirements are usually managed in dedicated requirements management packages. In these packages strict procedures and business processes are embedded according to the needs of the organisation, and regulatory requirements. It is not the intention to replace these systems, but instead to keep the requirements stored in the systems as the source data, and add additional collaborative information to these references, information such as models that satisfy them, studies that meet them. However in order to use the requirements in a collaborative environment, sufficient of the source information needs to be available for dissemination. Therefore the requirements have a textual definition, and optional associated documents and properties. There are two parts to the verification of requirements, the identification of the item that should be satisfied a Requirement; and the identification of items used as evidence of verification. These may also have a systems engineering context. &lt;example&gt;A System has a zonal breakdown, with requirements specific to the zone such as a maximum surface temperature for all items in that zone. Therefore every item in the zone should satisfy the requirement and each one should have a thermal analysis model as evidence that it has, or has not, satisfied the requirement. If the item is removed from the zone it no longer needs to satisfy the requirement.&lt;/example&gt; The Figure below provides an overview of this capability. &lt;figuresysml&gt;&lt;id&gt;_18_4_1_1b310459_1578993058900_906434_72179&lt;/id&gt;Overview of the Requirement capability&lt;/figuresysml&gt; </body>
      </ownedComment>
      <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590669293163_661379_73943" xmi:uuid="da55b635-85fe-4411-86eb-700ee8a44bf6" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
        <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733916_936964_15047"/>
        <body>Reference Data core_rd_v1#state of verification Named Individuals: verification planned; verification started. verification failed; verification insufficient evidence; verification qualitative estimation; verification logical proof; verification quantitative proof; verification standard reference; </body>
      </ownedComment>
      <name>RequirementVerification</name>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733534_160854_14174" xmi:uuid="13daa94d-92f4-4fab-ae13-7e3d8fa4bc08" xmi:type="uml:Association">
