      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733534_810142_14162" xmi:uuid="37edc7b7-f210-4ae0-ab45-f5937c74d2f3" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733906_187284_15030" xmi:uuid="f9852bbd-82b0-4f4d-8f54-b347ec529ff7" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733534_810142_14162"/>
          <body>A Requirement is an essential characteristic, condition, or capability that shall be met or exceeded by a system or a component to satisfy a contract, standard, specification, or other formally imposed document. &lt;note&gt;The term "requirement" is used here in the sense that term is used in systems engineering and similar industrial domains.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of RequirementObject therefore: &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;It is a type of VersionableObject therefore, it shall have at least one VersionIdentifiers property. This can be used to identify the version of the Requirement in a dedicated requirement management package;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyValues therefore, it may have PropertyValues specific to the requirement;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;It is a type of ProgrammeObject therefore, it may have Approvals, Assumptions, Justifications, Contracts and SecurityTrust information.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification that something should satisfy the Requirement is represented by RequirementShouldBeSatisfied.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification of the evidence needed to verify that something satisfies the Requirement is represented by Verification.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is used to define the objectives for a Study.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>Requirement</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733906_580630_15024" xmi:uuid="a86ba546-6309-4c7d-b32e-e21440f5b2a8" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
          <general xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733534_116015_14166"/>
        </generalization>
      </packagedElement>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508252526046_360111_47166" xmi:uuid="398fed49-84bf-4ef8-8132-d4e4d8d4e5cc" xmi:type="uml:Association">
