        <name>ArchitectureOfItem</name>
        <isAbstract>true</isAbstract>
        <ownedAttribute xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1562660170971_348945_50492" xmi:uuid="50216057-3cda-480d-b088-ed86258d787a" xmi:type="uml:Port">
          <name>architectureOfItem</name>
          <visibility>public</visibility>
          <type href="../../../Core_model/Collection/Collection.xmi#_18_4_1_1b310459_1581932043631_158459_57465"/>
          <aggregation>composite</aggregation>
        </ownedAttribute>
      </packagedElement>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733766_417425_14525" xmi:uuid="fd48096e-806e-49de-bd2c-1a0328de747a" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1583763718825_183000_72303" xmi:uuid="629e5a5e-9e89-47c3-a75c-922004c54a71" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1583763684879_490194_72294"/>
          <body>architecture inclusion membership UUID from ArchitectureElementInclusion subclassof core_v1#collection membership </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734036_30855_15676" xmi:uuid="ea182184-ea94-458c-877f-7f34f42f580b" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733766_417425_14525"/>
          <body>Enhancement: Include a role TBC. (Need an example to determine how this should be represented)</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734036_566352_15675" xmi:uuid="ebf134a5-46d1-492d-95c3-66f633be3d33" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733766_417425_14525"/>
          <body>The ArchitectureElementInclusion identifies something that is included in the Architecture and therefore part of the definition of the Architecture. &lt;note&gt;RequirementShouldBeSatisfied is used to indicate that it should satisfy a Requirement.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;An ArchitectureElementInclusion may be the referenced object of any ValueInstanceObject ValueOf therefore, providing the Architecture context for a DistributionValueInstance or KeyValueInstance.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;An ArchitectureElementInclusion may be referenced by a Justification, therefore, providing the Justification for the inclusion of something in an Architecture. It can also have Approvals.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;ComponentA in ArchitectureX should satisfy the Requirement for 30W heating, but in ArchitectureY only needs to satisfy a Requirement for 25W heating.&lt;/example&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>ArchitectureElementInclusion</name>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1511198948304_727664_39405" xmi:uuid="554e988e-190f-420e-815d-92c0c9a8ee2d" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1511199019071_723336_39409" xmi:uuid="07013cd2-a2b8-4cae-95ef-d0da88ef1c7e" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1511198948304_727664_39405"/>
            <body>an Architecture shall not include a Breakdown that references the same Architecture as an ArchitectureOf, also included Breakdowns shall not have a BreakdownElement that references the Architecture as an ArchitectureOf.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>NotCircular</name>
          <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733766_417425_14525"/>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1511198948304_562080_39406" xmi:uuid="12ec5476-c18d-497f-8af9-3a3ff4c33cc4" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>The architecture shall not include a Breakdown that has a BreakdownElement that the Architecture is an ArchitectureOf</body>
            <language>English</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734036_479106_15671" xmi:uuid="05f4eab6-dc3c-46a1-8d92-8a4df2ca63d1" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
