        <ownedAttribute xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734066_643147_15792" xmi:uuid="13e8832a-18bf-4d20-97df-9de122f6ed04" xmi:type="uml:Property">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1513759183169_282960_32624" xmi:uuid="2a4021dd-a723-4d6a-9ca7-9a0ae1de5a56" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734066_643147_15792"/>
            <body>the statistical moment properties that define the distribution. The value of this attribute need not be specified. &lt;example&gt;These are statistical moments 1. expected value, 2. variance, 3. skewness, 4. kurtosis.&lt;/example&gt;</body>
