      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_975971_14480" xmi:uuid="292cc101-749d-4b8b-b170-a5882f1ee1ba" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734016_741326_15609" xmi:uuid="09b981c1-f94f-4fd3-928e-a238c7ef7cd4" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_975971_14480"/>
          <body>An InterfaceConnectionType is the definition of a type of connection between ports of type InterfacePortType. It is referenced by an InterfaceConnectionInstance for a definition. &lt;note&gt;If the connection is directional, it is implied that the flow is from the object referenced by the "From" property and to the object referenced by the "To" property.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;The same InterfacePortType may be referenced by both the "From" and "To" properties. However the InterfaceConnectionInstance, for which the InterfaceConnectionType is the definition, shall reference different InterfacePortInstance though these may both have the same InterfacePortType definition.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of VersionableObject therefore, it shall have at least one VersionIdentifiers property.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of MethodologyObject therefore, it may define the specification using Documents.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyDefinitions therefore, it may have PropertyDefinitions.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It may reference instances of InterfaceTypeRealizationItem for definitions of objects that can realize the connection.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1588080379827_740297_78462" xmi:uuid="f55db79b-48d0-4d1e-98a2-27f408fd9179" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1588079311426_338604_77387"/>
          <body>realization collection subclass of core_v1#collection</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>InterfaceConnectionType</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1586181962765_493841_83559" xmi:uuid="11308ca4-a278-49db-b6e3-7914e7814db4" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
