      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_234303_14477" xmi:uuid="a3e43556-2599-456f-ab97-95dadae573ec" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734016_707832_15587" xmi:uuid="11b62457-196b-41bc-8ab5-6536e216beb3" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_234303_14477"/>
          <body>An InterfacePortRealizationAssociation is an association between an instance of InterfacePortInstance and the InterfaceInstanceRealizationItem that realizes the port. &lt;note&gt;Identification that the association is in the context of an Architecture is represented by ArchitectureElementInclusion.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;This can be a ModelInstance representation of the port such as a CAD model, a finite element model or a spreadsheet.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;example&gt;An AccessibleModelInstanceConstituent can be used when the item realizing the port in internal to the model, for example a publication in a CAD model, or a group of nodes or boundary conditions in a finite element model, or a named area in a spreadsheet.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt;</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1588006840883_709306_73649" xmi:uuid="d932476e-521e-4472-8608-a58c66f417fe" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
