      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_433662_14478" xmi:uuid="ae9c08b3-5eec-4150-a22a-35874abb90dd" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734016_519748_15598" xmi:uuid="e46b4ee3-e3f0-4b2d-a131-7e8e6da4fbac" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_433662_14478"/>
          <body>An InterfacePortInstance is a port on a PortTypeItem and may be connected to other ports using InterfaceConnectionInstance. The connection definition InterfacePortType is referenced using the IsAnInstanceOf property. &lt;note&gt;The InterfacePortType defines the type of port, but the InterfacePortInstance may have additional specification information about where it should be located on the PortTypeItem.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyValues therefore, it may have PropertyValues.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Links between an InterfacePortInstance and items that realize the connection are represented by InterfacePortRealizationAssociation.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;The PortRelationship is used to indicate relationships between ports with a choice of delegation, derivation, hierarchical.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;RequirementShouldBeSatisfied is used to indicate that it should satisfy a Requirement.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>InterfacePortInstance</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733886_140957_14867" xmi:uuid="17b8aa40-9333-408a-af0f-4804bd4d8546" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
