      </packagedElement>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_749408_14484" xmi:uuid="cdb04f5f-3dea-4ced-b037-ccf063137d04" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734026_46000_15637" xmi:uuid="9c37e3ed-d6e0-45ab-9b45-5f98a9e57ed2" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733756_749408_14484"/>
          <body>An InterfacePortType is the definition of the interface port on the PortTypeItem and may be connected to other ports using InterfaceConnectionType. It is referenced by an InterfacePortInstance for a definition. &lt;note&gt;The same InterfacePortType may be referenced by both the "From" and "To" properties of an InterfaceConnectionType. However the InterfaceConnectionInstance, for which the InterfaceConnectionType is the definition, shall reference different InterfacePortInstance though these may both have the same InterfacePortType definition.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of VersionableObject therefore, it shall have at least one VersionIdentifiers property.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of MethodologyObject therefore, it may define the specification using Documents.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ObjectWithPropertyDefinitions therefore, it may have PropertyDefinitions&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;A computer specifies ports for USB, a power, and video interfaces. These have their own spatial specification for the shape and size of the plug and socket. They may also have alternative spatial location specifications using either XYZ from a known origin or an orientation matrix.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;example&gt;The InterfacePortType for a Component specifies it will be a power port measured in watts. Different ComponentAssembleUsage of the Component can then specify the different values for power on different InterfacePortInstance.&lt;/example&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>InterfacePortType</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1586182398542_42847_83623" xmi:uuid="14693f4f-efce-414d-b85a-e2dc8185d0df" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
          <general xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733876_870517_14803"/>
        </generalization>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733886_438168_14839" xmi:uuid="47a483a9-561b-4777-ae2c-aa7ac93a8ddf" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
