      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734116_471735_15883" xmi:uuid="ef96925a-45a0-4e97-9864-de199774ce3a" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734676_563397_17730" xmi:uuid="9ff38ba3-1cf2-42c0-8f59-e27a49370b39" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734116_471735_15883"/>
          <body>A QualityReportType is the definition of a quality report managed at the collaborative level. &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ModelType therefore, identification of the items it is DerivedFrom is represented by ModelTypeIsDerivedFrom.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ModelType therefore, it has an InheritsFrom property. This may be either a QualityReportType or a ModelType, the latter modelling features to be part of the assessment of quality.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Many ModelTypeHasQualityReport may reference the same ModelType in the same or in different template contexts therefore, enabling different reports for the same ModelType.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;The same QualityReportType may be for more than one ModelType in the same or in different template contexts.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;There is no restriction in the use of QualityReportType in the audit trail therefore, a ModelType may be derived from QualityReportType.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576749899801_6672_61963" xmi:uuid="ad32a897-5411-441b-9f9f-fa409101ca37" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1549278630865_136333_44089"/>
          <body>quality report part subclass of ap243_v1#model part</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>QualityReportType</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734676_142616_17729" xmi:uuid="1bfe33cb-296e-4452-8a60-e52418f39800" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
          <general xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733656_615235_14225"/>
        </generalization>
