    <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_4661_14045" xmi:uuid="e144e034-b098-4547-aa6d-5842c31d9b78" xmi:type="uml:Package">
      <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512657025813_485201_32581" xmi:uuid="47de70d0-d20c-40e2-8c61-6a411b0d0295" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
        <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_4661_14045"/>
        <body>The study capability represents information for the management collaborative work that is launched to drive the evolution and maturity of something. A Study Manages AssociativeModelNetworks and may be hierarchical managing other Studies, or using other Studies and as an input or starting point. &lt;example&gt;A study may be for many reasons such as evolving the design; managing change; performing trade-off analysis; investigating sensitivity of a solution to Uncertainty; developing new methods and tools; combining results from other studies into a single baseline.&lt;/example&gt; The Figure below provides an overview of this capability. &lt;figuresysml&gt;&lt;id&gt;_18_4_1_1b310459_1578994126776_107399_75740&lt;/id&gt;Overview of the Study Management capability&lt;/figuresysml&gt; </body>
      </ownedComment>
      <name>StudyManagement</name>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1508329061156_615424_43393" xmi:uuid="02ede0be-677b-4545-bc75-deee521e5b05" xmi:type="uml:Association">
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1508329061156_5349_43394"/>
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1508329039621_402442_43368"/>
        <ownedEnd xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1508329061156_5349_43394" xmi:uuid="d1f92a7a-479a-4603-b973-d622050104b1" xmi:type="uml:Property">
          <visibility>private</visibility>
          <type xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733686_591537_14289"/>
          <association xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1508329061156_615424_43393"/>
        </ownedEnd>
      </packagedElement>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734356_444160_16373" xmi:uuid="0345baa1-a55a-4efc-879d-d08044e26eac" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1578486725928_261772_62598" xmi:uuid="13458774-4b8d-43f4-94fa-45bd7ddc633d" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1578490381124_755117_62812"/>
          <annotatedElement href="../../../Core_model/ManagementResources/ManagementResources.xmi#_2_attr_ProjectAssignment-Role"/>
          <body>Reference Data: actual work programme assignment</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1578486083754_934311_62253" xmi:uuid="39f19ce7-d1cf-4894-af73-6f96761b6de2" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1578485879118_845046_62210"/>
          <body>Reference Data: programme sub class of core_v1f#project</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734846_469387_18266" xmi:uuid="8eb829f7-6f0e-409b-8b0b-0b65a0168740" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734356_444160_16373"/>
          <body>The identification of the life cycle phase of an item being managed or evolved for a goal. &lt;note&gt;This is the identification of a Programme not a representation of all aspects and activities needed to achieve the goal for the item as that can include management of organization, resources, activities, scheduling planning as well as a the management of the development of item or family of items.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;A Breakdown may be a BreakdownOf a Programme.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;An Architecture may be an ArchitectureOf a Programme.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;A Programme may be the identified as a Requirement Source.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;A Programme may be a Study ProgrammeContext.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;example&gt;The concept phase of a particular aircraft programme.&lt;/example&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590668629795_481475_72760" xmi:uuid="d0f43e3f-a72d-4e94-9284-a264ce66495c" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733946_552527_15214"/>
          <body>Reference data core_v1#life cycle stage Named individuals: certification phase; concept stage; design phase; development stage; exploratory research stage; non-specific stage; production stage; retirement stage; support stage; systems engineering; utilization stage.</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>Programme</name>
        <ownedRule xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590668429859_19818_72576" xmi:uuid="3c6a0344-1cf7-4370-a7f9-9d907b3853ed" xmi:type="uml:Constraint">
          <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590668429861_323077_72578" xmi:uuid="f8ae2371-804b-4663-9945-82df5341ccdb" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
            <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1590668429859_19818_72576"/>
            <body>values shall be namedIndividual of the reference data class.</body>
          </ownedComment>
          <name>ProgrammePhaseConstraint</name>
          <constrainedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733946_552527_15214"/>
          <specification xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1590668429861_276757_72577" xmi:uuid="0bed4798-e6c6-43c3-9edd-e79243939489" xmi:type="uml:OpaqueExpression">
            <body>ProgrammePhase.mustBeNamedIndividualOf('http://standards.iso.org/iso/10303/-4000/tech/refdata/core_v1#a8535000-130a-0135-b552-598f1b1392ae')</body>
            <language>OCL2.0</language>
          </specification>
        </ownedRule>
