      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733836_770854_14698" xmi:uuid="fcf5a14c-6ac8-4d45-ba4a-c52dd0de79eb" xmi:type="uml:Association">
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734096_313693_15876"/>
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734086_490740_15830"/>
        <ownedEnd xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839734096_313693_15876" xmi:uuid="77538373-35bb-422b-9cb9-06c06151bf69" xmi:type="uml:Property">
          <visibility>public</visibility>
          <type xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733826_703030_14681"/>
          <lowerValue xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1584628367849_966765_77059" xmi:uuid="2300f2dc-4b44-44c0-a811-5eda19db972d" xmi:type="uml:LiteralInteger"/>
          <upperValue xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1584628367849_842818_77060" xmi:uuid="4fb3750c-652e-478e-82ae-463d0d6ec871" xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
            <value>*</value>
          </upperValue>
          <association xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733836_770854_14698"/>
        </ownedEnd>
      </packagedElement>
    </packagedElement>
    <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_562245_14046" xmi:uuid="fe855398-165a-4a05-9db8-7916e6d7f6ec" xmi:type="uml:Package">
      <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512657947996_914481_32648" xmi:uuid="fbce3513-14c8-4746-9df6-a6ef1697c621" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
        <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733474_562245_14046"/>
        <body>The ModelManagement capability enables the management of models and their traceability in a collaborative context. An AssociativeModelNetwork is a container that identifies the elements that together comprise a set of “results” for a Study. This includes the audit-trail of what is to be done, and what has been done. Each element in the AssociativeModelNetwork has an understanding of its dependencies (what it is derived from), and therefore, defines a network of associative models and key values. The elements may reference another element from which it is evolved. This is similar to versions but allows a branching, diverging and converging evolution, and therefore, multiple "latest" evolutions as different solution options are investigated simultaneously. This enables an evolution chain to be recorded across collaborating platforms with disconnected versioning. The Figure below provides an overview of this capability. &lt;figuresysml&gt;&lt;id&gt;_18_4_1_1b310459_1578992003318_834801_69137&lt;/id&gt;Overview of the Model Management capability&lt;/figuresysml&gt; </body>
      </ownedComment>
      <name>ModelManagement</name>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508490777486_274864_39378" xmi:uuid="06832cf0-8d86-4107-8655-2265eb87c99f" xmi:type="uml:Association">
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508490777487_161930_39379"/>
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508490756531_846999_39353"/>
        <ownedEnd xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508490777487_161930_39379" xmi:uuid="150cd184-ffad-48d1-abae-2e62aba93891" xmi:type="uml:Property">
