          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1509706085277_119134_45341"/>
          <body>UUID from AccessibleModelInstanceConstituent individual part accessible constituent subclass of core_v1#individual part</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1512561377966_386974_32720" xmi:uuid="e0f58980-f9bd-40cf-a3e3-f40fd22f6bf1" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733696_607128_14329"/>
          <body>An AccessibleModelInstanceConstituent represents something inside the ModelInstance (a constituent) that is made accessible. &lt;example&gt;The name of a surface publication in a CAD model; the number of a node in a finite element model; the name of a cell in a spreadsheet.&lt;/example&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject. The Identifiers or Names are used to identify the constituent.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification that a ModelTInstance is be derived from the constituent is represented by ModelInstanceIsDerivedFrom.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification that a ValueInstanceObject is be extracted from the constituent is represented by the property IsExtractedFrom.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It may be referenced as a realization of an InterfaceConnectionInstance or InterfacePortInstance.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <name>AccessibleModelInstanceConstituent</name>
        <generalization xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733966_320186_15333" xmi:uuid="4c2ecf72-5785-48a6-b2a2-9359b895a867" xmi:type="uml:Generalization">
