      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733706_13852_14331" xmi:uuid="527a2292-388c-451b-a596-d2ac7317fc32" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576677029910_530762_60958" xmi:uuid="0a8a5f3d-6e6a-4bc7-946d-691e3649f1fa" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1509377098149_811633_46866"/>
          <body>individual part version extracted from relationship sub class of: individual part version sequence relationship</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1585663997925_236625_82509" xmi:uuid="0e86cc70-970e-4ffa-a5ec-eef56e00b147" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <body>There is no object that links a CollectionMembership to a RealizedIndividualPart, therefore create a collection that contains the CollectionMembership and associate to the RealizedIndividualPart</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733966_6265_15363" xmi:uuid="249c2b23-1787-4401-84ff-3473cf53b943" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733706_13852_14331"/>
          <body>ValueInstanceObject is an abstract object used for monitoring and control of an AssociativeModelNetwork. &#13;They may either be single values (KeyValueInstance) or Distributions (DistributionValueInstance) &lt;note&gt;They are extracted from a ModelInstance or an AccessibleModelInstanceConstituent. It is logical that the ModelInstance is part of the same AssociativeModelNetwork, but this restriction is not imposed. New instances change which models they are extracted from as the programme life-cycle progresses, but their definition (KeyValueType) remains the same.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It BelongsTo one AssociativeModelNetwork.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It may have a ValueOf reference to the item the value represents.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It may be evolved from another ValueInstanceObject. The IsEvolvedFrom relationship is the equivalent of instance versions. Versions were not used because they imply a linear progression, where the evolution allows a diverging and converging progression, therefore, there may be more one "latest version".&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is assumed that the Person or Organization references ExecutorOf, SynchronizerOf and WatchersOf of the references IsExtractedFrom also apply. If the IsExtractedFrom reference is an AccessibleModelIInstanceConstituent, then the ModelInstance for which it is one of the Constituents is used. If the IsExtractedFrom is not specified, then the BelongsTo AssociativeModelNetwork is used.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ProgrammeObject therefore, it may have Approvals, Assumptions, Justifications, Contracts and SecurityTrust information.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;RequirementShouldBeSatisfied is used to indicate that it should satisfy a Requirement.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification that it is evidence needed to verify that something satisfies the Requirement is represented by Verification.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1585664535398_721664_82619" xmi:uuid="279b40b2-e87b-4ddb-9533-f2ca1a62fa20" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1509458846601_659619_37714"/>
          <body>value of Subclass of individual part version relationship subclass of breakdown element realization subclass of part version to individual part version association</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_13110319_1568731541836_788974_52353" xmi:uuid="47f75c3b-301f-475c-b52e-b8ee080c9dee" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733966_997016_15371"/>
          <body>AP243 question: include interfaces in ValueOfItem?</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576676688099_749294_60190" xmi:uuid="4e4b6981-4967-4c63-b9cb-206712bae3c1" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_13110319_1508428524334_796899_48198"/>
          <body>individual part version evolved from relationship sub class of: individual part version derivation relationship</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508496252660_762066_44977" xmi:uuid="700b6b63-0d6f-4bf0-b207-6c7823981eda" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508496086707_659883_44717"/>
          <body>mapping rationale: PartVersionToIndividualPartVersion rather than PartToIndividualPart because not all KVI versions will implement the same concept</body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1521627602719_551588_49544" xmi:uuid="a9dccb83-c482-4fbc-9675-ed486ca82e3d" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement href="../../../Core_model/IndividualPart/IndividualPart.xmi#_2_attr_PartToIndividualPartAssociation-AssociatedPart"/>
