      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508484569260_939481_34744" xmi:uuid="7c1a8bc3-6aca-4cc4-a008-7eb07c4ab588" xmi:type="uml:Association">
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508484569260_83000_34745"/>
        <memberEnd xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508484551819_886830_34719"/>
        <ownedEnd xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508484569260_83000_34745" xmi:uuid="42a96b18-dd53-4139-9add-3ecf9911fa08" xmi:type="uml:Property">
          <visibility>private</visibility>
          <type xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1505839733696_133644_14326"/>
          <association xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1508484569260_939481_34744"/>
        </ownedEnd>
      </packagedElement>
      <packagedElement xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1521623189131_365252_46766" xmi:uuid="829f294a-73b1-4976-81d0-b50b101bb5b6" xmi:type="uml:Class">
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1521623756704_989688_46914" xmi:uuid="2a95482d-c47d-4283-a9b4-6233bc00c4ee" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
          <annotatedElement xmi:idref="_18_4_1_1b310459_1521623189131_365252_46766"/>
          <body>A KeyValueInstance is a key piece of information available at the collaboration level. It is defined by a KeyValueType as represented by the IsAnInstanceOf property. &lt;note&gt;A KeyValueInstance may have a property Value containing the data value for the instance. This is need not be specified because during the planning phase of the life-cycle a KeyValueInstance represents the identification of a value that needs to be calculated.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;A KeyValueInstance is a type of ValueInstanceObject that is a type of AssociativeModelNetworkItem therefore, it shall have a BelongsTo property referencing an AssociativeModelNetwork.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;A KeyValueInstance is a type of ValueInstanceObject and therefore, may have an IsExtractedFrom property referencing a ModelInstance or AccessibleModelInstanceConstituent. The BelongsTo properties of the referenced objects may reference the same or a different AssociativeModelNetwork from that referenced by the KeyValueInstance. As the KeyValueInstance evolve during a programme life-cycle, new instances may change which type of ModelInstance each IsExtractedFrom, but their KeyValueType definition remains the same.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;The evolution of a KeyValueInstance through the programme life-cycle is represented by the IsEvolvedFrom reference property. This is similar to versions but allows a branching, diverging and converging evolution, and therefore, multiple "latest" evolutions as different solution options are investigated simultaneously.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is assumed that the Person or Organization references ExecutorOf, SynchronizerOf and WatchersOf of the references IsExtractedFrom also apply. If the IsExtractedFrom reference is an AccessibleModelIInstanceConstituent, then the ModelInstance for which it is one of the Constituents is used. If the IsExtractedFrom is not specified, then the BelongsTo AssociativeModelNetwork is used.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of IdentifiableObject therefore, it shall have Identifiers and may have a Descriptions, Names, other management information from ManagedObject.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;It is a type of ProgrammeObject therefore, it may have Approvals, Assumptions, Justifications, Contracts and SecurityTrust information.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;RequirementShouldBeSatisfied is used to indicate that it should satisfy a Requirement.&lt;/note&gt; &lt;note&gt;Identification that it is evidence needed to verify that something satisfies the Requirement is represented by Verification.&lt;/note&gt; </body>
        </ownedComment>
        <ownedComment xmi:id="_18_4_1_1b310459_1576677422409_224244_61566" xmi:uuid="f3e7b375-03ba-489e-840c-c887c8d764c0" xmi:type="uml:Comment">
